  cat <<EOF
Usage:
  kite audit [options] [target-directory]

Run dependency audits and basic security checks.

Options:
  --fix                Attempt to auto-fix audit findings
  -h, --help           Show this help text

Checks:
  - Committed .env files with potential secrets
  - Python dependency vulnerabilities (pip-audit)
  - JavaScript dependency vulnerabilities (npm/pnpm audit)

Monorepo support:
  Automatically discovers subprojects and audits each one.

Examples:
  kite audit .
  kite audit --fix .
EOF
}

release_help() {
  cat <<'EOF'
Usage:
  kite release prepare [options] [target-directory]
  kite release publish [options] [target-directory]
  kite release [options] [target-directory]

Prepare a release on a feature branch, then publish it from the default branch.
Without a subcommand, `kite release` is a legacy alias for `kite release publish`.

Prepare options:
  --bump TYPE          Version bump type: major, minor, patch (default: patch)
  --skip-checks        Skip `kite verify feature`, `kite test`, and `kite audit`
  --dry-run            Preview only (default behavior for prepare)

Publish options:
  --bump TYPE          Version bump type: major, minor, patch (default: patch)
  --confirm            Actually write version, changelog, commit, and tag
  --skip-checks        Skip publish-time test and audit gates
  --dry-run            Preview changes without writing (default when --confirm is omitted)
  -h, --help           Show this help text

Safety:
  `prepare` runs merge-readiness plus test and audit on the feature branch.
  `publish` runs test and audit again on the default branch before mutating.
  Release notes combine merged PR titles (when available) with the
  `[Unreleased]` changelog section.

Examples:
  kite release prepare .
  kite release prepare --bump minor .
  kite release publish --bump minor --confirm .
  kite release publish --bump major --confirm --skip-checks .
EOF
}

verify_feature_help() {
  cat <<EOF
Usage:
  kite verify feature [target-directory]

Pre-merge checklist for the current feature branch.

Checks:
  - Working tree clean
  - Not on default branch
  - No merge conflicts in tracked files
  - Active Speckit tasks file has all tasks marked done

Recovery:
  On failure, kite prints why the check matters, concrete next commands,
  and the matching docs/errors page.

Examples:
  kite verify feature .
EOF
}

